cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about credit card fraud detection using various supervised and unsupervised approaches. The main focus is on machine learning models and their performance evaluation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). However, the paper also involves machine learning algorithms, which can be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper uses a dataset that contains transaction details, which can be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it involves image and video processing.
